title: Alfred Hitchcock documentary from 1973!
description:
Episode from documentary series "The Men Who Made the Movies" about one of the most predominant film directors of the early 1900s. Includes scenes from various movies, such as Psycho, Birds and North by Northwest. This documentary contains rare interview material of Hitchcock, who was well known for avoiding being in front of the camera - except for the trademark passing appearances in his films.
